[See interview with Erik Lundblad from the Norwegian Red Cross Society, who is deputy team leader at the Red Cross Ebola treatment centre in Kono, at the source URL above.

According to WHO, Sierra Leone, which now has surpassed Liberia as the country with the most Ebola infections, has 9409 cases and 2732 deaths as of 27 Dec 2014.

