[The New York Times Science section [section D 30 Dec 2014] is devoted in its entirety to the 2014 Ebola outbreak after more than 20 000 cases and 7800 deaths [WHO data as of 28 Dec 2014].

How Ebola roared back
-------------------
Date: Mon 29 Dec 2014
Source: The New York Times [edited]
http://www.nytimes.com/2014/12/30/health/how-ebola-roared-back.html


Dr Pierre Rollin, the top Ebola expert at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, describes his efforts alongside other early responders from the World Health Organization [WHO] and Doctors Without Borders [MSF] to control the outbreak in W Africa.

Dr Peter Piot, who helped discover Ebola in 1976, and Jeremy Farrar, a British infectious disease specialist, called the West Africa outbreak "an avoidable crisis" in an editorial published online in September [2012] in The New England Journal of Medicine. In the same issue, WHO officials said of the March to July [2014] period that "modest further intervention efforts at that point could have achieved control."

[Byline: Kevin Sack reported from Atlanta; Sheri Fink from Liberia, Sierra Leone, Geneva and New York; Pam Belluck from New York; and Adam Nossiter from Guinea. The article was written by Mr Sack.

Graphics by Larry Buchanan, Jonathan Corum, Yuliya Parshina-Kottas, Sergio Pecanha, and Derek Watkins; produced by Craig Allen, David Furst, and Jacky Myint.

Photographs by Daniel Berehulak]

Excellent informative graphics including figures, maps, photos, and videos can be accessed in this source. - Mod.LK]
